│ My analysis indicates that the crash is due to an incorrect assumption in the              │
│ `instcombine` pass. The optimization logic for the `llvm.ptrmask` intrinsic correctly      │
│ identifies a `getelementptr` (GEP) operation on the pointer argument but fails to consider │
│ that this GEP can be a `ConstantExpr` (when operating on global variables) instead of a    │
│ `GetElementPtrInst`. The code then unconditionally casts the operand to                    │
│ `GetElementPtrInst`, leading to an assertion failure.                                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ To fix this, I will modify the code to handle both `GetElementPtrInst` and GEP             │
│ `ConstantExpr` cases. I will use `dyn_cast` to check the type of the GEP operand.          │
│ - If it's a `GetElementPtrInst`, I will use the existing `IRBuilder` to create a new GEP   │
│ instruction.                                                                               │
│ - If it's not an instruction, it must be a `ConstantExpr`. I will cast it to `GEPOperator` │
│ (a common base class) and use its `getWithNewIndices` method to create a new GEP constant  │
│ with the updated index.                                                                    │
│                                                                                            │
│ This approach ensures that both instruction and constant-expression forms of GEPs are      │
│ handled correctly, fixing the crash and making the optimization more robust.               │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will now apply this change.                                                              │
│                                                                                            │
